# Literature Review: A Novel Approach to the Behavioral Aspects of Cybersecurity

## Introduction

The rapid advancement of technology and the widespread use of the internet have made cyberspace
an inseparable aspect of everyone's life. Cyberspace refers to the online world that is separate from
everyday reality and is characterized by its interconnectedness and digital nature. However, with the
benefits of cyberspace also come various risks and challenges, particularly in the realm of cybersecurity.
Cybersecurity failures can have catastrophic consequences in financial aspects [1]–[6], high-tech industry
[7]–[13], and even life-threatening aspects in healthcare [14]–[20]. In order to mitigate these risks, it is
essential to understand the behavioral aspects of cybersecurity and the role of human factors in ensuring
information security.

## Human Errors and Lack of Knowledge in Cybersecurity

It is well-established that many cybersecurity failures are caused by human errors or their lack of
knowledge. Research has shown that individuals with internet addiction and impulsivity are more likely to
engage in risky cybersecurity behaviors [12]. Moreover, attitudes towards cybersecurity play a significant
role in determining an individual's cybersecurity practices [12]. Understanding the link between internet
addiction, impulsivity, attitudes towards cybersecurity, and risky cybersecurity behaviors can provide
valuable insights into developing effective cybersecurity strategies.

## Incorporating Complexity Science and Information Systems

Complexity science and information systems offer valuable contributions to saving human lives in the
context of cybersecurity. By applying complexity science principles, researchers have been able to better
understand the dynamics of cyberattacks and develop strategies to prevent and mitigate their impact [1].
Information systems, on the other hand, provide the necessary infrastructure and tools for collecting and
analyzing cybersecurity data [1]. By integrating complexity science and information systems, researchers
can gain a comprehensive understanding of cybersecurity threats and develop effective countermeasures.

## Design of Secure Water Treatment Systems

The design of secure water treatment systems is a critical aspect of cybersecurity, particularly in the
context of critical infrastructure. Research has demonstrated the importance of developing secure water
treatment systems and has provided datasets to support further research in this area [2]. These datasets can
be used to analyze and evaluate the vulnerabilities of water treatment systems, identify potential cyber
threats, and develop strategies to prevent and respond to cyberattacks.
