algorithms to simulate phishing attacks and train individuals to recognize and respond to such threats.
Integrating AI-based cybersecurity awareness training into educational programs and organizational
practices can enhance individuals' ability to detect and prevent phishing attacks.

## Internet of Things (IoT) and Cybersecurity

The Internet of Things (IoT) has revolutionized various industries, but it also introduces new cybersecurity
challenges. Research has emphasized the importance of addressing cybersecurity issues in IoT devices
and networks [15]. Detecting and mitigating cybersecurity attacks in IoT systems require the application
of AI methods [15]. Future research should focus on developing effective AI-based solutions for detecting
and preventing cybersecurity attacks in IoT environments.

## Conclusion

The behavioral aspects of cybersecurity play a crucial role in ensuring information security and mitigating
cyber threats. Human errors and lack of knowledge are significant contributors to cybersecurity failures,
highlighting the need for interventions that target internet addiction, impulsivity, and attitudes towards
cybersecurity. Incorporating complexity science and information systems can provide valuable insights
into the dynamics of cyberattacks and inform the development of effective countermeasures. Additionally,
research in the design of secure water treatment systems, fast malware classification, human factors in
cybersecurity, industrial critical infrastructure, AI in cybersecurity, and IoT cybersecurity contributes to
our understanding of the behavioral aspects of cybersecurity. Future research should address knowledge
gaps and explore potential research directions to further advance this field and enhance cybersecurity
practices.
